keyFacts: Ghislaine Maxwell had 58 recorded international travel entries in U.S. Customs systems between 1990 and 2020.
Her travel patterns show frequent flights between New York (JFK) and London (LHR) as well as Paris (CDG/ORY).
The document was generated on January 16, 2020, indicating active law enforcement monitoring of her movements prior to her July 2020 arrest.
Travel documents used include U.S. Alien Registration Card (I-), Passport (P), and INSPASS document.
Multiple U.S. departure points include JFK, Miami, Newark, Los Angeles, Dallas, Cincinnati, and Dulles airports.
